abstract: Republican-led House in Florida votes 72-to-41 to defeat bill to expand health coverage to as many as 650,000 uninsured residents; it marks third time Florida lawmakers have rejected health care expansion since passage of Affordable Care Act.
lead_paragraph: It was the third time that legislators had considered and spurned some version of health care expansion since passage of the Affordable Care Act.
